NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|It is a slight misnomer to do a "queen ask." What you are actually doing is asking for the queen or "extra length"  meaning you know you have at least a 10-card fit. Let me give a simple example. Suppose it goes 1S-P-2N (Jacoby)-P-4N-P-?. Let's say the 2N bidder has 2 key cards, and 5 spades but no queen. He would still respond 5S to 4N (showing 2 key cards and the "queen") because he knows their side has a 10 card fit, so they do not need to worry about the @SQ. So you always show the queen if you know your side has a 10 card or longer fit.|
